#DStv403​ #eNCA ETHEKWINI - The eThekwini municipality said it's looking at buying more poultry farms to help fight unemployment. Rainbow Chicken farms in KwaZulu-Natalback closed in 2017. READ: SA announces chicken imports tariffs At the time, the country's biggest chicken producer said it was under immense economic pressure because of chicken dumping, which created unfair competition for local producers. Following the closure, the municipality purchased one and started the Isukile Agricultural Cooperative, which employs previously retrenched workers. Taking Stock: The state of chicken farming & consumption in SA? The workers say they're looking at expanding their business and sell to other countries. Watch the video above for more details on this story.